<th colspan="2"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Persondata" title="Wikipedia:Persondata">Persondata</a></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="persondata-label">NAME</td>
<td>alal ad-Din Muhammad Rumi</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="persondata-label">ALTERNATIVE NAMES</td>
<td>Rumi; Mevlânâ Celâleddin Mehmed Rum; Mawlānā Jalāl ad-Dīn Muhammad Balkhī; Mawlana; Mawlana Rumi Rumi</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="persondata-label">SHORT DESCRIPTION</td>
<td>13th century Persian poet, jurist, theologian and teacher of <a href="/wiki/Sufism" title="Sufism">Sufism</a>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="persondata-label">DATE OF BIRTH</td>
<td>1207 CE</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="persondata-label">PLACE OF BIRTH</td>
<td><a href="/wiki/Balkh" title="Balkh">Balkh</a>, <a href="/wiki/Afghanistan" title="Afghanistan">Afghanistan</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="persondata-label">DATE OF DEATH</td>
<td>1273 CE</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="persondata-label">PLACE OF DEATH</td>
<td><a href="/wiki/Konya" title="Konya">Konya</a>. <a href="/wiki/Turkey" title="Turkey">Turkey</a></td>
</tr>
</table>
